      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1999 Porsche 911 Carrera 2 is a mechanically sound example of the analog 996.1 generation. It features the 3.4L M96 flat-six engine mated to a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) has been replaced. The chassis remains taut with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, providing the communicative feedback expected from a rear-engine, hydraulic-steering setup. The engine exhibits strong compression across all cylinders with no signs of bore scoring. Equipped with four-piston monobloc calipers and ventilated rotors, the braking system provides exceptional thermal management and bite. A well-sorted driver's car for the purist.",
